unicode-bom.option:
This rule has a string option:

- "always"files must begin with the Unicode BOM
- "never"(default) files must not begin with the Unicode BOM

always

Example ofcorrectcode for this rule with the"always"option:

﻿// U+FEFF at the beginning

/*eslint unicode-bom: ["error", "always"]*/

let abc;

Example ofincorrectcode for this rule with the"always"option:

/*eslint unicode-bom: ["error", "always"]*/

let abc;

never

Example ofcorrectcode for this rule with the default"never"option:

/*eslint unicode-bom: ["error", "never"]*/

let abc;

Example ofincorrectcode for this rule with the"never"option:

﻿// U+FEFF at the beginning

/*eslint unicode-bom: ["error", "never"]*/

let abc;
